==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stirring
<hw>Stir"ring</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Putting in motion,
or being in motion; active; active in business; habitually employed in
some kind of business; accustomed to a busy life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A more <qex>stirring</qex> and intellectual age than any which had
gone before it.</q> <rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Animating; arousing; awakening; stimulating;
quickening; exciting.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stirrup</ent>⟦br⟧
